{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "ComputeStrangeAttractor",
  "description": "Strange Attractor — particles integrate through one of five chaotic ODEs (Lorenz, Rössler, Aizawa, Thomas, Halvorsen) using a JSON-editable WGSL compute kernel. The graph is organized for legibility: the main pipeline flows from Seed Particles through Particle Integration (the core wgsl_compute kernel), diffusion, rendering particles to texture, tone mapping, and display transformation. Parallel control logic derives the attractor type (clip-trigger cycling plus manual selection via mux), camera angles for 3D projection (time-scaled rotation), and particle count and brightness compensation from canvas size. All groups flatten to the original byte-identical behavior; node IDs are preserved and card bindings reach inner nodes by their stable nodeId unchanged.",
